column1: 1. If Sequence Format Column is not added or having blank data then 'NA' format is selected for transaction.

2. If Invoice having multiple product details then add multiple rows having same 'Default Global Items'/'Global Custom Items' Data and different as per your details of 'Default Line Items'/'Line Level Custom Items'.
3. Import file must have first row with having column header 'T'/'L' ('T' -  'Default Global Items'/'Global Custom Items' and 'L' - 'Default Line Items'/'Line Level Custom Items'.
4. If Custom Field Item having 'Multi-Select Drop Down' then the values should differentiate by semicolon (;).
5. If Custom Field Item having 'Check List' then values for the sequence should provide in true/false differentiate by semicolon (;).
6. If Custom Field Item having 'Check Box' then values should be 'true'/'false'.
7. In import wizard pick the right matching  'Date Format'.
